This paper is primarily focused on networking and data center architecture, which suggests that it belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The paper also discusses the challenges of routing and physical layout, which are relevant to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of a random graph topology and the comparison to a fat-tree suggest that this paper could also be classified under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
